
We distinguish between stateless and stateful widgets in Flutter because stateless widgets don’t
change theyre perfect for UI elements that won’t update. Stateful widgets, on the other hand, a
re for UI elements that do change or update like a counter, form input, 

Use a Stateless widget for content that stays the same after it's built, like text or icons.
Use a Stateful widget when you need to track user input or change the UI based on user interactions.
